Occitanie, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Bours","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Camille, Antoine, Cecile, Emile, Alcide, Anatole, Clovis, Ferrel, Leonce, Onile.","French: topographic name for someone who lived in a town as opposed to one who lived in a village, from Middle French <i>bourg</i> (Old French <i>burc</i>) ‘fortified town’, or a habitational name from (Le) Bourg, the name of several places in various parts of France. Compare   Bourke  ,   Bourque  ,   Burk  , and   Burke  .","History: Antoine Bourg/Bourque from Martaizé in Vienne, France, married Antoinette Landry in Acadia <i>c.</i> 1642. His descendants also bear altered forms of the surname, such as <i>Bourke</i>, <i>Bourque</i>, and <i>Burk(e)</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Bourgeois","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Marcel, Emile, Alphonse, Armand, Camille, Gaston, Monique, Pierre, Lucien, Michel, Normand.","French: from <i>bourgeois</i> ‘burgher’ (from Old French <i>burgeis</i>, from <i>burc</i> ‘fortified town’), a status name for an inhabitant and (usually) freeman of a fortified town (see   Bourg  ). Compare   Lebourgeois   and also   Boss  ,   Burgess  , and   Bushway  .","History: Jacques Bourgeois from France married Jeanne Trahan in Acadia <i>c.</i> 1643. Pierre Bourgeois from Poligny in Jura, France, married Marie-Louise Cléroux in Saint-Vincent-de-Paul, QC, in 1753."]},{"name":"Bourke","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Dermot, Liam, Murphy.","Irish: variant of   Burke  .","Americanized form of French   Bourg   or of its altered form   Bourque  ."]},{"name":"Bourget","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Normand, Jacques, Lucien, Pierre, Aime, Andre, Fernand, Germaine, Laurent, Ludger, Marcel, Marcell.","French: topographic name, a diminutive of   Bourg  , or a habitational name from (Le) Bourget, the name of several places in various parts of France.","Altered form of French <b>Bourgeais</b>, a variant of   Bourgeois  ."]},{"name":"Boulerice","meanings":["Altered form of Breton <b>Bourhis</b>: from <i>bourc'his</i> ‘burgher’, a status name for an inhabitant and (usually) freeman of a fortified town (see   Bourg  , compare   Bourgeois  )."]},{"name":"Bourque","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Lucien, Pierre, Andre, Aurele, Camille, Emile, Fernand, Henri, Jacques, Marcel, Normand.","French (mainly Doubs): variant of   Bourg   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this.","History: The (majority of the) American bearers of the surname <i>Bourque</i> are descendants of Antoine Bourg/Bourque from France (see   Bourg  )."]}]},{"name":"Guislaine","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Old French: oblique case of   Giselle  , in a spelling that suggests Dutch or Flemish influence."],"variants":[{"name":"Ghislain","meanings":["Of recent origin, or at any rate a recent introduction to the English-speaking world. It is evidently a revival of the Old French oblique case of   Giselle  , in a spelling that suggests Low German, Dutch, or Flemish influence."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Guislaine De Bours was born in 1115, in Bours, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, her father, Alexis de Bours, was 27 and her mother, Henriette de Nédon, was 17. She had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Alexandre De Thérouanne. She died in 1159, in Thérouanne, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, at the age of 44."},"et":{"1115–1159":"1115–1159","–1183":"–1183","–1184":"–1184","–1198":"–1198","1105–1169":"1105–1169","1136–1189":"1136–1189","1138–1195":"1138–1195","1138–1196":"1138–1196","1088–1147":"1088–1147","1098–1152":"1098–1152","1088":"1088","1198":"1198","1098":"1098","1152":"1152","1196":"1196","1195":"1195","1184":"1184","1183":"1183","1138":"1138","1105":"1105","1115":"1115","1159":"1159","1136":"1136","1147":"1147","1114":"1114","1169":"1169","1189":"1189","Thérouanne, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Thérouanne, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Thérouanne, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Bours, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Bours, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Bours, Hautes-Pyrénées, Occitanie, France":"Bours, Hautes-Pyrénées, Occitanie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1115–1159":"1115–1159","–1183":"–1183","–1184":"–1184","–1198":"–1198","1105–1169":"1105–1169","1136–1189":"1136–1189","1138–1195":"1138–1195","1138–1196":"1138–1196","1088–1147":"1088–1147","1098–1152":"1098–1152","1088":"1088","1198":"1198","1098":"1098","1152":"1152","1196":"1196","1195":"1195","1184":"1184","1183":"1183","1138":"1138","1105":"1105","1115":"1115","1159":"1159","1136":"1136","1147":"1147","1114":"1114","1169":"1169","1189":"1189","Thérouanne, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Thérouanne, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Ranska","Thérouanne, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Ranska","Bours, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Bours, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Ranska","Bours, Hautes-Pyrénées, Occita